            <title>[LU-16660] don&apos;t show grace time if this quota type is disabled</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16660</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If quotas disabled(i.e. enabled=none), but soft limit has been hit, lfs quota still shows grace period and an asterisk&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; near the usage. It is confusing from the user point of view as quotas are disabled. This could be simply fixed in utils - don&apos;t print grace period and an asterisk when appropriate quota type is disabled.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
